<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="590" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d590">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.002/18.]</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 73.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Sir: I have the honor to inform the Department that the newly appointed
                            Cabinet of Dr. Francisco Andrade Marin, President of the Chamber of
                            Deputies, in charge of the Executive Power, is as follows: Minister of
                            Foreign Relations, Señor Antonio Arcos; Minister of War, General Juan
                            Francisco Navarro; Minister of Hacienda, J. F. Intriago; Minister of the
                            Interior, Dr. José Maria Ayora; Minister of Public Instruction, Dr. Léon
                            B. Becerra.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Rutherfurd Bingham</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>